[{"id":"VR834521","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">A parallel plate capacitor consists of two plates separated by a distance <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"d\"><math alttext=\"d\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>d</mi></math></span></span>. The capacitor is connected to a battery so that there is a potential difference <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"delta V\"><math alttext=\"delta V\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Î”</mi><mi>V</mi></math></span></span> between the plates. The capacitor is then disconnected from the battery and isolated. While the capacitor is disconnected, the plates are moved together until they are a distance <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"d over 2\"><math alttext=\"d over 2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mfrac><mi>d</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math></span></span> apart. How do the magnitude of the electric field between the plates and the electric potential energy stored in the capacitor change, if at all, when the plates are moved closer together?</p><div class=\"table_wrapper\"><table class=\"tgroup align:center cols:3 colsep:0 frame:none rowsep:0\"><col class=\"colspec align:center colname:col1 colnum:1 colsep:1 colwidth:40\"/><col class=\"colspec align:center colname:col2 colnum:2 colwidth:70\"/><col class=\"colspec align:center colname:col3 colnum:3 colwidth:80\"/><thead class=\"thead\"><tr class=\"row rowsep:1\"><th class=\"entry colname:col1\"></th><th class=\"entry colname:col2\">Electric Field Magnitude</th><th class=\"entry colname:col3\">Electric Potential Energy</th></tr></thead><tbody class=\"tbody valign:middle\"><tr class=\"row\"><td class=\"entry colname:col1\">A</td><td class=\"entry colname:col2\">Increases</td><td class=\"entry colname:col3\">Increases</td></tr><tr class=\"row\"><td class=\"entry colname:col1\">B</td><td class=\"entry colname:col2\">Increases</td><td class=\"entry colname:col3\">Decreases</td></tr><tr class=\"row\"><td class=\"entry colname:col1\">C</td><td class=\"entry colname:col2\">Stays the same</td><td class=\"entry colname:col3\">Increases</td></tr><tr class=\"row\"><td class=\"entry colname:col1\">D</td><td class=\"entry colname:col2\">Stays the same</td><td class=\"entry colname:col3\">Decreases</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n","rubricRef":"VR834521_rubric","choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">A</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">B</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">C</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">D</p>"],"answer":3}]